entry.title: Disappointment, Fear Cloud Zimbabwe Election
entry.content: Zimbabweans cast their ballots in an election clouded by years of dizzyingly high inflation as well as intimidation from a ruling party that has been in power for more than four decades.

entry.title: Ukraine's Reset: A Slow and Bloody Advance on Foot
entry.content: After the failures of the initial armored assaults, which were blunted by Russian defenses, Kyiv resorted to small units attacking one position at a time.
